    "description": {
      "value": "<p><strong>Creature Type.</strong> You are a Humanoid.<br /><br /><strong>Size.</strong> You are Medium.<br /><br /><strong>Speed.</strong> Your walking speed is 30 feet.<br /><br /><strong>Darkvision.</strong> You can see in dim light within 60 feet of you as if it were bright light and in darkness as if it were dim light. You discern colors in that darkness only as shades of gray.<br /><br /><strong>Beasthide Shifting.</strong> As a bonus action, you can assume a more bestial appearance. This transformation lasts for 1 minute, until you die, or until you revert to your normal appearance as a bonus action. When you shift, you gain the following benefits:</p><ul><li>Temporary hit points equal to 2 Ã— your proficiency bonus.</li><li>You can roll 1 Hit Die and gain additional temporary hit points equal to the result. While shifted, you have a +1 bonus to your Armor Class.</li></ul><p>You can shift a number of times equal to your proficiency bonus, and you regain all expended uses when you finish a long rest.</p><p>Starting at 5th level, when you are reduced to 0 hit points but not killed outright while shifted, you can drop to 1 hit point instead. Your transformation immediately ends as a result. Once you use this trait, you cannot do so again until you finish a long rest.<br /><br /><strong>Bestial Instincts.</strong> Channeling the beast within, you have proficiency in one of the following skills of your choice: Acrobatics, Athletics, Intimidation, or Survival.<br /><br /><strong>Feral Impulses.</strong> You have advantage on saving throws you make to avoid or end the blinded, defeaned, and weakned condition on yourself.</p>",
      "chat": ""
    },
